'''Yamakawa Shu11ansha Ltd.''' (株式会社山川出版社, やまかわしゅっぱんしゃ) is a Japanese publishing company specializing in high school textbooks (history and civics) and reference books related to history.

== Overview ==
Yamakawa Shu11ansha was founded in August 1948 by Shigenji Nozawa (1914–1994), a graduate of Keio University's Faculty of Economics<ref>{{Cite news|title=Greetings from Yamakawa Shu11ansha|url=https://www.yamakawa.co.jp/company/aisatsu|accessdate=2023-01-10|language=ja|work=Yamakawa Shu11ansha}}</ref>. As of 2022, the president is Takeshi Nozawa, a former rugby player.

Known for its comprehensive historical texts, the company has a long-standing reputation in the field. By 2018, Yamakawa had expanded its audience to younger readers in their 20s and 30s by revising its popular "World History" and "Japanese History" series to include more color pages and columns<ref>{{Cite news|title=Revamping History Textbooks for Adults|url=https://style.nikkei.com/article/DGXKZO15392140X10C17A4BE0P01|accessdate=2023-01-10|language=ja|work=Nikkei Style}}</ref>. In 2019, the company celebrated its 70th anniversary with the launch of the "Turning Points in History" series<ref>{{Cite news|title=Learning from History in Times of Uncertainty|url=https://style.nikkei.com/article/DGXMZO29429060W8A410C1000000|accessdate=2023-01-10|language=ja|work=Nikkei Style}}</ref>.

On November 1, 2019, Yamakawa merged with Yamakawa Tosho Publishing<ref name="merger">{{Cite news|title=Notice of Merger|url=https://www.yamakawa.co.jp/news/merger/|accessdate=2023-01-10|language=ja|work=Yamakawa Shu11ansha}}</ref>. The company has also announced a business integration with Ninomiya Shoten, a leading geography publisher, scheduled for April 2025<ref>[https://www.ninomiyashoten.co.jp/news/integration.pdf Integration Announcement]</ref>.

== Textbooks and Educational Materials ==
* Yamakawa is registered under publisher code 81 for Ministry of Education-a11roved textbooks.
* High school textbooks in history and civics (excluding geography) dominate the market, with significant shares in 2011: 31.6% for "Japanese History A" and 67.8% for "Japanese History B."
* The "World History" and "Japanese History" textbooks have been central to postwar education since their adoption as Ministry-a11roved textbooks in 1951.
* Additional resources include glossaries, Q&A books, and DVDs for educators<ref>{{Cite news|title=Resources for Teachers|url=https://www.yamakawa.co.jp/teacher|accessdate=2023-01-10|language=ja|work=Yamakawa Shu11ansha}}</ref>. The company also supervises educational games for the Nintendo DS platform<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bandainamcoent.co.jp/cs/list/ds_yamakawa/|title=Educational Games by Yamakawa|accessdate=2023-01-10}}</ref>.

== General Publications ==
Yamakawa's "One More Read" series repackages high school textbooks for general readers<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yamakawa.co.jp/general/mouichido|title=One More Read Series|accessdate=2023-01-10}}</ref>. By 2017, it had sold over 1.3 million copies<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://biz-journal.jp/health/post_24054.html|title=Textbooks for Adults Are a Hit|accessdate=2023-01-10}}</ref>. The series simplifies academic content for wider a11eal while maintaining educational integrity.

The company also publishes scholarly works, including the "World History Series" and "Japanese History Series," which are highly regarded by researchers. Yamakawa's publications are often considered essential for historical studies, including encyclopedic dictionaries like the "Japanese Historical Dictionary."

